Blessed is the man who does not walk in the advice of the wicked;
nor does he stand in the way of sinners;
nor does he sit in the assembly of mockers.

I will tell the decree;
Yahweh said to me:
“You are my son;
today I have begotten you.

Rise up, O Yahweh; deliver me, O my God;
for you strike all my enemies on the cheek.
The teeth of the wicked you break.

For there is not anything reliable in his mouth;
their inner part is destruction.
Their throat is an open grave;
with their tongue they speak deceit.

I am weary with my groaning;
I flood my bed every night.
With my tears I drench my couch.

let the enemy of my soul pursue,
and overtake and trample my life into the ground,
and lay my honor in the dust. Selah

The enemies are destroyed in ruins forever,
and you have uprooted their cities;
their very memory has perished.

Yahweh has made himself known;
he has executed judgment.
The wicked is snared by the work of his hands. Higgaion Selah

His mouth is filled with cursing,
with deceits and oppression;
under his tongue are trouble and evil.

He sits in ambush in villages;
in the hiding places he kills the innocent.
His eyes lurk for the helpless.

He lies in ambush secretly, like a lion in a thicket.
He lies in ambush to seize the poor;
he seizes the poor by catching him in his net.

Rise up, O Yahweh;
O God, lift up your hand.
Do not forget the afflicted.

In Yahweh I have taken refuge;
how can you say to my soul,
“Flee to your mountain like a bird”?

Yahweh is in his holy temple;
Yahweh is in the heavens on his throne.
His eyelids see;
they test the children of humankind.

For Yahweh is righteous;
he loves righteous deeds.
The upright shall see his face.

Save, O Yahweh, for the pious have ceased to be;
for the faithful have vanished
from among the children of humankind.

All have gone astray;
they are altogether corrupt.
There is not one who does good;
there is not even one.

You have tried my heart;
you have examined me by night;
you have tested me; you found nothing.
I have decided that my mouth will not transgress.

from the presence of the wicked who destroy me,
those enemies against my life,
they that surround me.

He made darkness his hiding place;
all about him his covering
was a darkness of waters, thick clouds.

Yahweh has rewarded me according to my righteousness;
According to the cleanness of my hands
he has repaid me.

You rescued me from strife with people;
you set me as head (over) nations.
People I did not know served me;

Its rising is from one end of the heavens
and its circuit to the other end of them;
and nothing is hidden from its heat.

All who see me mock me.
They open wide their lips;
they shake the head, saying:

Do not be far from me
because trouble is near;
because there is no helper.

My strength is dry like a potsherd,
and my tongue is sticking to my jaws;
and you have placed me in the dust of death.

Because dogs have surrounded me;
a gang of evildoers has encircled me.
Like the lion they are at my hands and my feet.

because he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted,
and has not hid his face from him;
but he listened to him when he cried for help.

Who is the king of glory?
Yahweh, strong and mighty;
Yahweh, mighty in war!

Yahweh is my light and my salvation;
whom shall I fear?
Yahweh is the refuge of my life;
of whom shall I be afraid?

The voice of Yahweh is over the waters;
the God of glory thunders.
Yahweh is over many waters.

You are my hiding place;
from trouble you preserve me.
With cries of deliverance you surround me. Selah

Do not be like a horse or like a mule, without understanding;
that needs his tackle—bridle and rein—for restraint
or he would not come near you.

But at my stumbling they rejoiced and gathered together;
smiters whom I did not know gathered against me.
They tore and did not cease.

I was a youth, but I am now old;
yet I have not seen the righteous forsaken
or his children begging for bread.

My heart grew hot inside me;
in my sighing a fire burned.
Then I spoke with my tongue,

Surely a man walks about as a mere shadow;
surely in vain they bustle about.
He heaps up possessions but does not know who will gather them in.

And when one comes to see me, he speaks falsely;
his heart gathers disaster for itself.
He goes out to the street; he speaks.

My tears have been my food day and night,
while they say to me all day long,
“Where is your God?”

O my God, within me my soul is in despair;
therefore I remember you from the land of Jordan
and the heights of Hermon, from the mountain of Mizar.

My heart is moved with a good word;
I recite my compositions to the king.
My tongue is the pen of a skilled scribe.

You are the most handsome of the sons of humankind;
grace is poured out on your lips;
therefore God has blessed you forever.

Your arrows are sharp;
peoples fall under you
in the midst of the king’s enemies.

God is in the midst of her;
she will not be made to totter.
God will help her at daybreak.

He makes wars cease to the ends of the earth;
he breaks the bow and cuts off the spear.
The wagons of war he burns with fire.

Be still, and know that I am God.
I will be exalted among the nations;
I will be exalted in the earth.

Let Mount Zion rejoice;
let the daughters of Judah rejoice
because of your judgments.

Surely God will ransom my life
from the power of Sheol,
because he will receive me. Selah

These things you have done, and I have been silent;
You imagined that I was just like you.
I will rebuke you and present an argument before your eyes.

He who sacrifices a thank offering honors me,
and he who orders his way;
I will show him the salvation of God.”

Deliver me from the guilt of bloodshed, O God,
the God of my salvation;
then my tongue will sing aloud of your righteousness.

The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit;
A broken and contrite heart,
O God, you will not despise.

“Look, the man who would not make God his refuge,
but he trusted in the greatness of his wealth;
he took refuge in his destructiveness.”

I will freely sacrifice to you;
I will give thanks to your name,
O Yahweh, because it is good.

We who would take sweet counsel together;
in the house of God
we would walk with the throng.

You have kept count of my wonderings.
Put my tears in your bottle;
are they not in your book?

He will send from heaven and save me;
he will reproach the one who tramples me. Selah
God will send his loyal love and his faithfulness.

They have set a net for my steps;
my soul is bowed down.
They have dug a pit before me;
they have fallen into the midst of it. Selah

My heart is steadfast, O God;
My heart is steadfast.
I will sing and give praise.

Awake, my glory;
Awake, harp and lyre.
I will awake the dawn.

Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine,
and Ephraim is the helmet for my head;
Judah is my scepter.

Moab is my washing pot;
over Edom, I will cast my sandal.
On account of me, O Philistia, raise a shout.”

Trust him at all times, O people;
pour out before him your heart.
God is a refuge for us. Selah

Once God has spoken;
twice I have heard this:
that strength belongs to God.

He turned the sea into dry ground;
they passed through the river on foot.
There we rejoiced in him.

He rules by his might forever;
his eyes keep watch on the nations.
Do not let the rebellious exalt themselves. Selah

God settles the lonely in a home;
he brings prisoners out into prosperity.
But the rebellious abide in a barren land.

Be for me a rock of refuge to resort to always;
you have ordained to save me,
because you are my rock and my fortress.

We give thanks to you, O God;
we give thanks, and your name is near.
Your wonderful deeds are told.

The stouthearted are plundered;
they sleep their sleep,
and all the able men cannot use their hands.

Make vows and fulfill them to Yahweh, your God;
let all surrounding him
bring tribute to the one to be feared.

In the day I have trouble, I seek the Lord.
At night my hand stretches out continually;
my soul refuses to be comforted.

Waters saw you, O God;
waters saw you and they trembled.
Surely the deeps shook.

The sound of your thunder was in the whirlwind;
lightnings lit the world;
the earth shook and quaked.

O God, the nations have entered your inheritance;
they have defiled your holy temple;
they have reduced Jerusalem to ruins.

Do not remember against us former iniquities;
let your mercies meet us quickly
because we are brought very low.

In this trouble you called, and I rescued you.
Within the secret place of thunder I answered you;
I tested you at the waters of Meribah. Selah

Because Yahweh God is a sun and a shield;
Yahweh gives grace and honor.
He does not withhold good from those who walk blamelessly.

My eye languishes from misery.
I call on you, O Yahweh, every day;
I spread out my hands to you.

He will call upon me and I will answer him;
I will be with him in trouble;
I will rescue and honor him.

The rivers have lifted up, O Yahweh;
the rivers have lifted up their rumbling;
the rivers have lifted up their pounding.

You who love Yahweh, hate evil.
He protects the lives of his faithful;
he delivers them from the hand of the wicked.

And the strength of the king loves justice.
You have established equity;
you have executed justice and righteousness in Jacob.

Moses and Aaron were among his priests;
Samuel also was among those who called on his name.
They called to Yahweh, and he answered them.

Know that Yahweh, he is God;
he made us and we are his.
We are his people and the sheep of his pasture.

How many are your works, O Yahweh;
all of them you have done in wisdom.
The earth is full of your creatures.

He remembers his covenant forever,
the word that he commanded
for a thousand generations,

Gilead is mine. Manasseh is mine.
And Ephraim is the helmet for my head.
Judah is my scepter;

Moab is my washing pot.
Over Edom I will cast my sandal;
Over Philistia I will shout in triumph.”

Because he wore a curse as his robe,
let it enter his body like water,
and into his bones like oil.

He will judge among the nations;
he will fill them with corpses.
He will shatter the rulers of many countries.

He has sent redemption to his people;
he has commanded his covenant forever;
holy and fearful is his name.

The fear of Yahweh is the beginning of wisdom;
all who do them have a good understanding.
His praise endures forever.

Praise Yah!
Blessed is the man who fears Yahweh;
he takes great delight in his commands.

He gives lavishly to the needy;
his righteousness endures forever.
His horn rises high in honor.

they have their hands, but they cannot feel,
their feet, but they cannot walk;
they cannot utter a sound in their throats.

Yahweh remembers us; he will bless us.
He will bless the house of Israel;
he will bless the house of Aaron.

Ah, Yahweh, I am indeed your servant;
I am your servant, the child of your maidservant.
You have loosed my bonds.

They surrounded me like bees;
they were extinguished like a fire of thorns.
In the name of Yahweh I opposed them indeed.

The sound of rejoicing and salvation
is in the tents of the righteous;
the right hand of Yahweh has done valiantly.

He causes clouds to rise from the edge of the earth;
he makes lightnings for the rain;
he brings out the wind from his storehouses.

Yahweh accomplishes things for my benefit.
O Yahweh, your loyal love endures forever;
do not abandon the works of your hands.

Let burning coals fall on them;
let them be dropped into the fire,
into bottomless pits from which they cannot rise.

look to my right and see.
There is no one looking out for me;
there is no escape for me;
no one cares for my soul.

I remember the days of long ago;
I meditate on all your doings.
I muse on the labor of your hands.

Teach me to do your will, for you are my God;
your Spirit is good.
Lead me onto level ground.

Stretch out your hands from on high;
Rescue me and deliver me from many waters,
from the hand of foreigners,

who executes justice for the oppressed,
who gives food for the hungry.
Yahweh sets prisoners free;

Yahweh opens the eyes of the blind;
Yahweh raises up those bowed down;
Yahweh loves the righteous;

Praise Yah.
For it is good to sing praises to our God;
for it is pleasant; praise is fitting.

Praise Yah.
Praise Yahweh from the heavens;
praise him in the heights.

let them praise the name of Yahweh,
because his name alone is is exalted.
His splendor is above earth and heavens.

to execute on them the judgment that is decreed.
This will be honor for all his faithful ones;
Praise Yah.

Praise Yah.
Praise God in his sanctuary;
praise him in his mighty firmament.
